OL,3,CThe welsh boxer banned from competing
OL,4,Cfor British title because he was black
OL,6,FCuthbert Taylor was a boxing pioneer
OL,7,Fin the 1920s and 30s. He was the first
OL,8,Fblack boxer to represent Great Britain
OL,9,Fat the Olympic Games in 1928. However,
OL,10,Fhe never had the chance to be
OL,11,Frecognised as the best in Britain.
OL,13,FThe British Boxing Board of Control
OL,14,F(BBBofC) banned non-white boxers from
OL,15,Fcompeting for the British title. The
OL,16,F'colour bar rule', in place between
OL,17,F1911 and 1948, stated a fighter had to
OL,18,Fhave two white parents.
